ata":143,"value_category_id":7,"doc_id":13,"doc_url":14,"form_type":16},"Mayer Brown LLP",7046,113239,"I will continue to participate in this defined contribution plan, but the plan sponsor no longer makes contributions. (2016-07-01)",{"description":21,"appointee_id":22,"dsid":133,"endnote":7,"entity_id":24,"id":145,"income_amount":7,"income_category_id":7,"income_type":7,"line_no":32,"metadata":146,"value_category_id":7,"doc_id":13,"doc_url":14,"form_type":16},113238,"I will continue to participate in this defined contribution plan, but the plan sponsor no longer makes contributions. (2019-06-01)",{"description":21,"appointee_id":22,"dsid":122,"endnote":148,"entity_id":24,"id":149,"income_amount":7,"income_category_id":7,"income_type":7,"line_no":26,"metadata":150,"value_category_id":7,"doc_id":13,"doc_url":14,"form_type":16},"As a partner at the law firm of King & Spalding LLP, the legal services I provide are subject to District of Columbia Bar Rule of Professional Conduct 1.6 (DC Rule 1.6) and Wisconsin Bar Rule of Professional Conduct 1.6 (WI Rule 1.6) on confidentiality of information. DC Rule 1.6 prohibits knowingly revealing a confidence or secret of a client, including the identity of a client or the fact of such representation. WI Rule 1.6 prohibits revealing information relating to the representation of a client, including the identity of a client or the fact of such representation, even if the identity of the client has already been disclosed in public. See Wisconsin Formal Ethics Opinion EF-17-02. Notwithstanding this, I have disclosed representations of clients where the client consented to the disclosure. I provided services to six additional clients who are entities where DC and/or WI Rule 1.6 applies and where disclosure of the client identity and the fact of representation would reveal a client confidence or secret and/or information relating to the representation of a client.",113242,"Services as Partner",{"description":152,"appointee_id":22,"dsid